EchoBubble v0.1

What’s new
- Consent screen before any synthesis
- First-tap voice picker per sender (saved mapping)
- Foreground bubble overlay (reliable on Android 8+)
- Auto-start overlay when a new message arrives
- Proper notification channel for playback
- One-click build + install scripts (Windows/Linux/macOS)

How to install (quick)
1) Run the TTS server on your PC (uvicorn app:app --host 0.0.0.0 --port 8000)
2) adb reverse tcp:8000 tcp:8000
3) Set Api.kt base URL to http://127.0.0.1:8000
4) Install app-debug.apk
5) Open app → Accept consent → Grant Notification Access + Draw Over Apps
6) Share a voice note to EchoBubble to create a voice → tap bubble on new messages

Notes
- Local and free if you run the TTS server yourself (XTTS v2)
- On Android 9+, allow cleartext or use HTTPS (ngrok works)
- Debug: a button in the app can start the bubble manually
